<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="594" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1310,1681]" box="[151,612,1310,1337]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,612,1310,1337]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,612,1310,1337]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">
<taxonomicName box="[151,262,1310,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of economic interest
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1310,1681]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">
The most widespread 
<taxonomicName box="[395,492,1344,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[395,492,1344,1368]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of economic importance is 
<taxonomicName box="[804,941,1344,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaneeckei">
<emphasis box="[804,941,1344,1368]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">L. vaneeckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lily-bulb thrips that was described from Europe but which has been moved around the world by the horticultural trade in bulbs and orchids. Three other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,280,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,280,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have also been reported as localized plant pests. 
<taxonomicName box="[831,996,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oleae">
<emphasis box="[831,996,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips oleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a pest of olive trees in the European Mediterranean countries (
<bibRefCitation author="Moritz" box="[426,628,1448,1472]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" refString="Moritz, G., Mound, L. A., Morris, D. C. &amp; Goldarazena, A. (2004) Pest thrips of the world - visual and molecular identification of pest thrips. Cd-rom published by Lucidcentral. org (Brisbane). ISBN 1 - 86499 - 781 - 8." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Moritz 
<emphasis box="[508,555,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[646,803,1448,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adisi">
<emphasis box="[646,803,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips adisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a pest of the commercial liane 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Paullinea cupana</emphasis>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[269,337,1484,1507]" name="Brazil" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[398,616,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="austriacus">
<emphasis box="[398,616,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips austriacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been implicated as a pest of 
<taxonomicName box="[988,1075,1484,1507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Pistacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[988,1075,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Pistacia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
crops in 
<collectingCountry box="[1183,1226,1484,1507]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" refString="Minaei, K. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2014) The Liothrips - lineage of thrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae) from Iran with the first record of micropterous morph of a Liothrips species Zootaxa, 3889 (1), 107 - 117." type="journal article" year="2014">Minaei &amp; Mound 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, three species in this genus have been investigated as biocontrol agents of weedy plants, 
<taxonomicName box="[1341,1436,1518,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urichi">
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">L. urichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
against 
<taxonomicName authority="Simmonds 1933" authorityName="Simmonds" authorityYear="1933" box="[233,589,1552,1576]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[233,389,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Clidemia hirta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simmonds" box="[402,580,1553,1576]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" refString="Simmonds, H. W. (1933) The biological control of the weed Clidemia hirta, in Fiji. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 24, 345 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300031655" type="journal article" year="1933">Simmonds 1933</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[600,726,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikaniae">
<emphasis box="[600,726,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">L. mikaniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
against 
<taxonomicName authority="Cock 1982" authorityName="Cock" authorityYear="1982" box="[813,1161,1552,1576]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Mikania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis box="[813,1019,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Mikania micrantha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cock" box="[1032,1153,1553,1576]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" refString="Cock, M. J. W. (1982) The biology and host specificity of Liothrips mikaniae (Priesner) (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae), a potential biological control agent of Mikania micrantha (Compositae). Bulletin of Entomological Research, 72, 523 - 533. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300013705" type="journal article" year="1982">Cock 1982</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1216,1353,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tractabilis">
<emphasis box="[1216,1353,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">L. tractabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
against 
<taxonomicName authority="Mound &amp; Pereyra 2008" authorityName="Mound &amp; Pereyra" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,783,1587,1611]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Campuloclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrocephalum">
<emphasis box="[151,505,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Campuloclinium macrocephalum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[518,775,1588,1611]" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" refString="Mound, L. A., &amp; Pereyra, V. (2008) Liothrips tractabilis sp. n. (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripinae) from Argentina, a potential biocontrol agent of Weedy Campuloclinium macrocephalum (Asteraceae) in South Africa. Neotropical Entomology, 37, 63 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 566 X 2008000100009" type="journal article" year="2008">Mound &amp; Pereyra 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1049,1587,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1049,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported here as damaging 
<taxonomicName box="[1340,1435,1587,1611]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Jatropha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1340,1435,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Jatropha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[179,260,1623,1646]" name="Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">
<collectingRegion box="[179,260,1623,1646]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Mexico</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
is of considerable potential interest in economic entomology because of increasing interest in the cultivation of 
<taxonomicName box="[180,275,1657,1681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Jatropha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="594" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,275,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="594">Jatropha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a profitable crop.
</paragraph>
